  "prompt": "Can white hairs turn into black?",
  "response": "White hairs cannot turn back to black once they have lost their pigment. Hair color is determined by pigment-producing cells called melanocytes, which can stop producing melanin as we age or due to other factors. When these cells become inactive, hair grows in without pigment, resulting in white or gray hair.\n\nHowever, there are anecdotal reports and some studies suggesting that stress or certain lifestyle changes might temporarily affect hair color, but these instances are not well-documented or understood. In some cases, addressing nutritional deficiencies or health issues can lead to improvements in hair health, but this typically does not reverse already white hair back to its original color.\n\nIf you're experiencing changes in hair color and are concerned, it's always a good idea to consult with a healthcare professional or a dermatologist.",
